reviewText: Sure, it's 1980's stuff, but that's what makes it so great.  Basic fun moves with Kathy and an upbeat group.

reviewText: This is the DVD version of three previous workouts.  It includes Winning Workout, Body Basics, and Fat Burning Workout.  If you have even two of these already, it's still worth purchasing.  It's the price of one workout, and you get to update your VHS--pretty soon we won't be able to work out to VHS anymore.  Video players are getting increasingly difficult to find.Kathy Smith's workouts are always top quality, and her personality takes me in without my wanting to turn off the voice.  The eighties are coming back again, so I think you'll get a kick out of it.
Title: N/A

reviewText: This workout is obviously taken from some of her earliest dvds and you only need to look at the fashions to tell. Not that there was anything wrong with the 80's and 90's, but exercise has changed since then and the outfits certainly have. No one wears sweat bands and g-string leotards over bike pants anymore. It's ridiculous. There are much better and newer Kathy dvds out there. Give this one a miss.
summary: Scraping the barrel with this one - this dvd was WAY too old for me
Title: N/A

reviewText: You get a bang for your buck!  Three great workouts (approx. 195 minutes)- and as everyone says getting past the hair and OMG those ourfits :OI have three DVD's from the Classics series and find that Kathy was ahead of her time with many of her exercises. The floor work is tried, true and effective. Some of the arobics are a bit high impact for me (no make that alot high impact) - so I tone it down to save my knees. The insturctions along with the do's and don'ts keeps you in check while you are going through the moves. The fifties dance routine is just sooooo corny but I found myself doing it and laughing. For the pirce this belongs in anyones collection.
Title: N/A

reviewText: I have had this DVD for a while and I absolutely LOVE the fat burning workout. I am young but i have terrible feet and some back issues and a lot of newer aerobic workout DVDs and videos are high impact and give my flat feet a lot of pain. this workout is the perfect low impact, medium intensity, longer length video.plus, it's actually pretty fun--as opposed to a lot of good workouts that are so intense that they are rewarding yet miserable.kathy smith is positive and likeable. i wish there were more videos like these out there.

reviewText: Fun workouts from previously released VHS workouts.  My only complaint would be the quality of the DVD, obviously copies of the VHS.  For the price, the quality should have been better.  If you don't mind the lower quality picture, this is a great workout DVD.
